Toledo Widens Lead in Peru Presidential Poll, Ipsos Apoyo Says

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-02-14T02:37:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/toledo-widens-lead-in-peru-presidential-poll-ipsos-apoyo-says.html
Former Peruvian President  Alejandro Toledo  widened his lead in an opinion poll ahead of the
presidential election in April, Ipsos Apoyo said.  Toledo, who led the Andean country for one five-year term
ending in July 2006, had 28 percent support, compared with 27
percent last month and 16 percent in October, according to
results of an Ipsos Apoyo survey announced by Lima-based America
Television today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in  Lima  at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 